access: Access to everything. Except the one closet which will be locked and the vintage Danish Modern dresser (family heirloom).
additional_house_rules: - No Shoes in the house whatsoever, but you will need them in the garden. No loud noise/music past 10pm. Walls are thin and our neighbors are close friends of ours so they will let you know.. lol. And they also will help with any questions you have. Everyone in the building is very lovely.
description:
Williamsburg, Brooklyn: Eclectic, bohemian, French, Southwestern would best describe our place. I like walking through the apt and each room has it's own style. We are  2 blocks to the L train Bedford stop. Step outside and you are surrounded with the most adorable, delicious, artistic and one of a kind restaurants, coffee shops, boutiques and of course the fun and interesting people watching. 10min subway to Manhattan or cab. Neighborhood is covered in art murals so have your cameras ready :)

Each room has its own uniqueness and theme :) Railroad Apt.

Access to everything. Except the one closet which will be locked and the vintage Danish Modern dresser (family heirloom).

I will definitely be reachable at all times. :)

Our street and neighborhood is stunning. Very iconic Brooklyn with brownstone buildings lining the street. Looks like a film set. Tons of cafes, restaurants and shopping.

L train Bedford stop is 2 blocks away (3min walk), 10 mins to Manhattan or cab about the same time.

hosts.about: Happy and chill married couple. We both work in the film/entertainment world, so we are here, there and all over sometimes. But always available to take your call, email or text. Hoping to get more travel in, but also enjoy being tourists in our own town. There is always somewhere to go, eat, and watch in NYC. We love it here and that is why it is home :)
